          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> is the rate-of-change of </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Velocity" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Velocity</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> with respect to time.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Notes</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: If you double the speed of a machine, then the maximum </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Acceleration-Nominal" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">nominal acceleration</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> of the parts will increase by four-times. The Parts must reach two times the velocity in half the time.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Cam-Laws" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Traditional Motion-Laws</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> are frequently named with reference to shape of the acceleration profile.</text></para>
        </td>
